    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "You say the \"against\" stance is \"grounded in pragmatic need,\" but isn't it also true that if we don't regulate now, the risk of an existential catastrophe becomes an actual certainty rather than just a theory? It feels like the \"pro-regulation\" side is just following the science on safety.",
