      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are fundamentally correct; proponents like Nick Bostrom aren't just risking innovation, they are actuarially following the science that small strategic risks stack into near-certainty over decades. Relying on ad-hoc future regulation is dangerous because by the time an existential threat becomes a proven certainty, the窗 of opportunity to mitigate it may already be closed. Therefore, genuine pragmatism actually demands immediate, robust pre-commencement governance rather than waiting for catastrophic results. The \"against\" argument loses its heart when it prioritizes preserving AGI governance over securing human survival itself.",
